cs.GT, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.LG, cs.MA

The paper deals with fair division problems, which are typically studied in the field of computational social choice (cs.GT). The use of a pricing mechanism to implement fair outcomes suggests a connection to mechanism design and algorithmic game theory (cs.AI). The discontinuity and complementarities of preferences suggest a need for careful analysis of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The study of multiple goods and cake cutting suggests a connection to optimization and algorithms (cs.LG) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA).
